<div class="grey-bcg flex">
    <div class="flex content-line">
        <div class="flex-vert mw-60">
            <h4><a href="https://github.com/szuhi27/ActivityManager" target="_blank" class="cyan-text">ActivityManager</a></h4>
            <p>I made a software to record activities, where you can start an activity, and stop it when it ends, and the program calculates the length of the activity. First I made it with Unity, then as a C# console application and finally as an ASP.NET Core web app. The first two times I used JSON as storage, and EF Core (SQL) was used for the web app. I made it to practice programming and also to see the differences between different methods.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="img-box flex">
            <div class="flex-vert">
                <img class="pr-img" src="~/images/projects/activity-manager/console.jpg" onclick="getElementById('modal-image').src = this.src;" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#imageDisplay" />
                <img class="pr-img" src="~/images/projects/activity-manager/web.jpg" onclick="getElementById('modal-image').src = this.src;" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#imageDisplay" />
            </div>
            <img class="pr-img" src="~/images/projects/activity-manager/unity.jpg" onclick="getElementById('modal-image').src = this.src;" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#imageDisplay" />
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

